The paper deals with the problem of reconstructing and segmenting multiple non-rigid structures from images, which is a common problem in computer vision and robotics. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves optimization and subspace clustering, which are common in the fields of robotics (cs.RO) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also deals with 3D reconstruction (cs.GR) and uses sparse affine combinations (cs.MM), which are common techniques in computer graphics and multimedia.
